</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="33" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="33">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4117874" author="Edmonds, JM" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" pagination="95 - 113" refId="B6" refString="Edmonds, JM, 1972. A synopsis of the taxonomy of Solanum Sect. Solanum (Maurella) in South America. Kew Bulletin 27 (1): 95 - 113, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4117874" title="A synopsis of the taxonomy of Solanum Sect. Solanum (Maurella) in South America." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4117874" volume="27" year="1972">Edmonds (1972)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the holotype of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. tweedieanum" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" rank="species" species="tweedieanum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">S. tweedieanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was held at K; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barboza, GE" editor="Anton, AM" journalOrPublisher=") Flora Argentina (Vol. 13), Solanaceae. IOBDA-IMBIV, CONICET: Buenos Aires &amp; Cordoba, Argentina" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" pagination="231 - 264" refId="B3" refString="Barboza, GE, Knapp, S, Saerkinen, T, 2013. Grupo VII. Moreloide. In: Anton, AM, Zuloaga, FO, Eds., Barboza GE (coord.) Flora Argentina (Vol. 13), Solanaceae. IOBDA-IMBIV, CONICET: Buenos Aires &amp; Cordoba, Argentina: 231 - 264" title="Grupo VII. Moreloide." volumeTitle="Barboza GE (coord." year="2013">Barboza et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
repeated this citation but added reference to a single sheet (K000585739). This is not effective lectotypification under Art. 9.23 of the Code (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany Monographs" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" refId="B20" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, W-H, Li, D-Z, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prado, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress, Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koelz Botanical Books, Glaeshutten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress, Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koelz Botanical Books, Glaeshutten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). The specimen cited as holotype by 
<bibRefCitation author="Barboza, GE" editor="Anton, AM" journalOrPublisher=") Flora Argentina (Vol. 13), Solanaceae. IOBDA-IMBIV, CONICET: Buenos Aires &amp; Cordoba, Argentina" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" pagination="231 - 264" refId="B3" refString="Barboza, GE, Knapp, S, Saerkinen, T, 2013. Grupo VII. Moreloide. In: Anton, AM, Zuloaga, FO, Eds., Barboza GE (coord.) Flora Argentina (Vol. 13), Solanaceae. IOBDA-IMBIV, CONICET: Buenos Aires &amp; Cordoba, Argentina: 231 - 264" title="Grupo VII. Moreloide." volumeTitle="Barboza GE (coord." year="2013">Barboza et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
and selected as lectotype here (K000585739) has open flowers and several buds and is a better match for the illustration in the protologue than the other sheet at Kew (K000585738); both specimens are annotated &quot;S. Tweedianum Hook./Bos. Ayres. Cult.&quot; in W.J. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hooker’s">Hooker's</normalizedToken>
handwriting and bear the herbarium stamp &quot;Herbarium Hookerianum/1867&quot; indicating they come from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hooker’s">Hooker's</normalizedToken>
own herbarium. There is no evidence on the specimens themselves that they were taken from the plants cultivated in Glasgow mentioned in the protologue, nor that they were collected prior to 1835; but the top part of the stem mounted on the sheet we have selected as the lectotype at Kew (K000585739, https://plants.jstor.org/stable/pdf/10.5555/al.ap.specimen.k000585739) is an excellent (mirror-image) match for Tab. 3385 in the protologue (
<bibRefCitation author="Hooker, WJ" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" refId="B8" refString="Hooker, WJ, 1835. SolanumTweedianum. Curtis's Botanical Magazine 62: Tab. 3385." title="SolanumTweedianum. Curtis's Botanical Magazine 62: Tab. 3385." year="1835">Hooker 1835</bibRefCitation>
; see https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/14341#page/36/mode/1up) suggesting it does represent original material. The original, and all subsequent, spelling of the name was 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Tweedianum”">&quot;Tweedianum&quot;</normalizedToken>
where John 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Tweedie’s">Tweedie's</normalizedToken>
name was implicitly latinized as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Tweedius”">&quot;Tweedius&quot;</normalizedToken>
in which the terminal vowel was eliminated. This is not acceptable under Art. 60.9(a)(1) of the Code (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany Monographs" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" refId="B20" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, W-H, Li, D-Z, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prado, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress, Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koelz Botanical Books, Glaeshutten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress, Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koelz Botanical Books, Glaeshutten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
) and the name should be formed as &quot; 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="tweedieanum" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" rank="species" species="tweedieanum">tweedieanum</taxonomicName>
&quot; (e.g., Art. 60.9, Ex. 31, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany Monographs" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" refId="B20" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, W-H, Li, D-Z, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prado, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress, Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koelz Botanical Books, Glaeshutten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress, Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koelz Botanical Books, Glaeshutten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
